# .azignore — documentation hidden from the in-app About (AzNavRail `azAbout` reader).
#
# AzNavRail's About reader auto-discovers every *.md in the repo root and under docs/.
# List patterns here to exclude developer/internal docs from the in-app About TOC.
# Format (like .gitignore): one pattern per line; `#` comments; exact paths
# (CHANGELOG.md), directory prefixes (docs/internal/), or globs (*.draft.md).
#
# Kept visible to end users: README.md, Changelog.md, PrivacyPolicy.md.

# Developer / AI-agent / internal root docs
AGENTS.md
GEMINI.md
BACKLOG.md
TODO.md

# The entire docs/ tree is developer-facing: architecture, code maps, algorithms,
# agent guidelines, release/CI runbooks, internal feature specs, and superpowers plans.
docs/
